<br>
Sorry I'm cranky about this, Kundow and I had a big discussion last night and I covered a lot of things that annoy the hell out of me, and rangers whining about auto attack was one of the BIG things. There are more than enough bad rangers out there. Archery auto-attack would just make it worse. Kundow and I both have seen rangers that are higher level than us who can't handle half of what we can. I got a pair of Hoppers dumped on me by a 56 ranger. As long as I'm FM when I start, I can handle four at once.<br>
<br>
There's a LOT of ranger issues that need fixing worse than auto-attack. There's no reason Wolf Form and Force of Nature shouldn't stack, for example, but they don't. I have to choose between regen and speed. The Brell's buffs still overwrite the superior Warder's Protection in some circumstances. Certain epic drops are almost non existant, even moreso than the infamous Pegasus Feather Cloak.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, with the pathing fix, does this mean they're going to completely recode Mistmoore? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=447262&amp;resize=truenewwindow">Kolani Stormynytes, Pathfinder of Tunare</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kolanistormynytes>KolaniStormynytes</A> at: 3/9/03 3:32:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takkonsmakafu>Takkon Smakafu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/9/03 3:46:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3907.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's the end of the world as we know it...</span><hr size=1> FYI fixing pathing is the final stage of Sony phasing monks out of the game. <p>&quot;Who is ya daddy...and what does he do?&quot;<br>
